-- Chilean Stocks: CCU, Colbun, Endesa and Enjoy Were Active
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2012-04-04T20:07:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-04/chilean-stocks-ccu-cias-cic-and-vina-concha-toro-are-active.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Santiago.  The  Ipsa index  fell 0.4 percent to 4,634.73. The  MSCI Chile
index (MXCL)  retreated 0.9 percent to 2,653.04.  Cia Cervecerias Unidas SA (CCU)   fell 2.1 percent to
7,330.1 pesos, its second day of losses. Chile’s largest brewer
had its recommendation cut to hold from buy at Deutsche Bank AG.  Colbun SA (COLBUN)   advanced 0.5 percent to 141.18 pesos,
reversing an earlier loss of 1.3 percent. Chile’s  Supreme Court 
rejected injunctions filed by opposition lawmakers and
environmental groups to block the HidroAysen power project being
developed by Colbun and Empresa Nacional de Electricidad SA, or
 Endesa. (ENDESA)   Endesa (ENDESA)  (ENDESA CC) also reversed earlier losses to close
little changed at 885.96 pesos.  Enjoy SA (ENJOY)   fell 4.5 percent to 105 pesos, the
biggest fall in almost five months. The Santiago-based casino
owner is meeting terms of its bonds after using 14.9 billion
pesos ($31 million) of a 17 billion-peso loan facility from its
controlling shareholder, according to a statement to the
securities regulator yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
